This paper discusses optimization methods for training deep neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the Adam optimization algorithm and proposes new variants of it, which suggests that it could also fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper mentions applications in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), which are related fields. Finally, the paper involves analyzing and improving algorithms, which could also fall under the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
